<p>Young Cabernet's aggressive tannins gradually polymerize, creating silky texture while preserving structure. Primary blackcurrant and cassis flavors evolve into complex secondary notes: leather, tobacco, cedar, and graphite. Tertiary aromatics emerge after 15+ years—forest floor, truffle, and dried herbs. The wine's color shifts from deep purple-black to brick-red at the rim, signaling proper development.</p>

